        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 7:46PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 746 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Osceola, or near Mishawaka, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Elkhart, Mishawaka, Goshen, Dunlap, Granger, Middlebury, Osceola,
Wakarusa, Millersburg, New Paris, Benton, Woodland, Jimtown,
Southwest, Foraker, and Waterford Mills.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
